      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine, collector-quality condition. This example features the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and a double-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been meticulously serviced to factory tolerances. The chassis is structurally sound with documented subframe reinforcement, ensuring the integrity of the rear floor under torque load. Power is managed via a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a variable M differential lock for optimal mechanical grip. The exterior retains its deep factory luster with no evidence of road rash or clear coat failure, while the interior Nappa leather remains supple and free of bolster wear. Mechanically, the vehicle is turn-key, exhibiting zero oil seepage from the constant pressure valve or valve cover gasket. This is a concours-ready specimen for the discerning purist.",
